      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even a small amount of alcohol can interact unpredictably with prescription sleep aids like zolpidem. Alcohol is a central nervous system depressant, and mixing it with a sedative will enhance its effects, potentially leading to over-sedation and impaired judgment. You should absolutely avoid even a single glass of wine before taking your medication to ensure your body processes the drug as intended. If you want to relax, try a warm herbal tea instead of mixing alcohol with your sleep aid.",
      "source": "target",
