      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The idea that alcohol enhances medication absorption is a dangerous myth; in reality, it disrupts how your body metabolizes drugs. Even an hour later, alcohol metabolites are still active and can significantly potentiate the sedative effects of zolpidem. The risk of unexpected side effects, like severe dizziness or blackouts, is too high to ignore. Stick to the plan and take your medication on an empty stomach, free from alcohol.",
      "source": "target",
